Content: For each order of any type of card, the card details are sent the next day by SMS to your phone number by the credit card company with a secure link to the virtual card details for digital use until the physical arrival of the card. The digital card can be used in businesses by connecting to a digital wallet or in online purchases, making the card useful for purchases even before the card physically arrives. It is not possible to withdraw money using a digital card
will need to activate the card in the app through the [cards page](https://app.tfd-bank.com/portfolio/cards) Or in [isracard website](https://digital.isracard.co.il/products-services/card-activation/). If you received your credit card in the mail or from your bank's office, you can also activate it by calling 036364432. Debit cards are activated on the next day. The card can be used within 24 hours of activation. A text message will be sent to you as soon as the credit card company activates it.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Ordering a card', 'Header 3': 'Why you need to have a card', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: To complete the account-opening process, you need to order a card. As a digital bank without physical branches, the only way to access your money is with the card, which is issued as soon as you open the account. Each customer can order one card of any type: debit or credit (depending on the bank's approval). In order for your application to be examined, you must first approve your consent for a credit report. For each customer in each bank account, at least one card and at most one card of each type (credit card and debit card) can be issued. You can order new card on the [cards page](https://app.tfd-bank.com/portfolio/cards). Navigate to the Cards page, where you can manage your existing cards and order new ones. If you don't have a card linked to your account, ordering a new card is free of charge. However, if you are replacing an existing card, there might be a fee depending on your subscription plan. You can follow the prompts to select the type of card you need, whether it's a credit card or a debit card, and confirm the order.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Card Delivery and Activation Process', 'Header 3': 'Card shipping companies and delivery time and identification', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: You can view the card delivery details only when ordering the card. At any other time, this information can be obtained by contacting a [private banker](/actions/attach_agent).
The cards at ONE ZERO Bank are sent to customers via a service called Quick to Mailbox in partnership with Israel Post. With this service, the card you ordered will be sent directly to your mailbox according to your updated mailing address in the bank's systems. The card will be sent within 7 business days. Once the card arrives, you will receive an SMS indicating that the card is waiting for you in your mailbox. Only after you collect it will you be able to activate it through the bank's application or with Isracard, at your choice.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Credit Cards vs. Debit Cards Similarities and Differences', 'Header 3': 'Debit card billing and limits', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: Debit cards are regularly debited from the account, but transactions made on the card wait for final approval 3 business days until they are actually charged and therefore reserve funds from line of credit. Debit transactions made on the same day usually add up to one total charge. The full details of transactions can be viewed on the Isracard website/app 48 hours after the execution of the transaction. Your debit card deducts charges immediately from your checking account after the payment. Debit card charges are deducted from the account on an ongoing basis, but transactions made on the card wait 3 business days for final approval before they are actually charged, therefore, the amount on the account is reserved.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Card Actions', 'Header 3': 'Unarranged overdraft and blocked cards', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: A frozen card cannot be used until the card is unfrozen. When a card is frozen, any future or installment charges will continue to be charged on time according to the original terms of the transaction. Reactivating a blocked card depends on the type of block: if it is blocked and canceled, it cannot be reactivated at all. You can order a new card easily on the [cards page](https://app.tfd-bank.com/portfolio/cards) -> click on the Order button -> choose the Order a New Card option -> select credit card or debit card. If the card is frozen contact our private bankers for assistance.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Ordering a card', 'Header 3': 'Correcting Spelling mistakes on Received Cards', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: If you received a card with spelling errors, to correct the writing with the credit card company, please send a request to the private banker and specify your name in English, or alternatively attach a photo of your passport showing your name, and the credit card company will send you a new card with the correct details. If your last name on the card doesn't appear in full, it might be because there is a maximum character limit of 20 characters, in which case, the last name will be shortened.

