Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Credit Cards vs. Debit Cards Similarities and Differences', 'Header 3': 'Double Charges and Unrecognized Charges in Debit Card', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: If you see a double charge and/or an unrecognized charge in your account and you are using a Debit card, it is important for us to update you of a few things: A Debit card is an immediate debits card that relies on the available balance in the account, performing transaction in this card will be immediately reflected in the app under "Non-Final Movements". The transaction charge is definitively descending from the account within 4-5 business days. Charges that appear as "double" or "unrecognized" are likely temporary (up to 24 hours) and are pending the final approval of the transaction in the bank's systems. We recommend that you regularly monitor your account and wait before contacting us regarding unrecognized or double charges.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Card Transactions Issues', 'Header 3': 'Duplicate and unrecognized transactions', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: If you have duplicate transactions on your card and need more information, contact a [private banker](/actions/attach_agent). If you see duplicate transactions in your account that were not made by you, you can dispute the transaction by going to the [cards page](https://app.tfd-bank.com/portfolio/cards), tapping More Actions, selecting Dispute Transactions, choosing the requested transaction and the reason for the dispute ("I was charged twice"). The credit card company clarify with the business, and at the end of it, the credit card company will update you.

Source: {'Header 1': 'ONE ZERO Bank Guide on Card Usage and Services', 'Header 2': 'Foreign currency card transactions on credit cards and debit cards', 'Header 3': 'Immediate debits from foreign websites', 'source': 'cards.md'}
Content: Transactions that are charged directly from a checking account are sometimes transactions made on foreign websites and therefore are charged immediately, instead of on the upcoming billing day. If you have further questions about why your credit card payment wasn't charged on your monthly billing day, you can contact a [private banker](/actions/attach_agent) for assistance.

